It is said that the poem was written at the request of Augustus; but it is no mere flattery of a reigning house. The supremacy of the Julian family was identified in the mind of the poet and his readers with the culmination of the Roman State in victory and peace, the predestined consummation of ages of vicissitudes and sn‘uggles.

The subject of the AEneid is the destruction of Troy, the seven years' wandering of AEneas, and his settlement in Italy, with the wars raised against him by the native princes»,
